Properties.Name: Family Design
Properties.Value:
The Southwest Solutions Group casework line is designed to be highly flexible and adaptable with every Revit model built to reflect its real world counterpart. Once loaded, each model has a variety of parameters which allow you to easily manipulate and customize various aspects of the casework design without ever needing to load a type catalog ever again.

System Overview

Custom applications comprised of specially fabricated, stainless steel equipment or pre-fab modular components, or a combination of both, work their way quickly through a simple yet sophisticated design, approval and fabrication process. Equipment built to your exact specifications, pre-wired and pre-plumbed (if applicable), is shipped with shorter lead times and at a lower overall cost.

Properties.Name: Technical Data
Properties.Value:
Countertops

  • 16 or 14 gauge, type 304 or 316 stainless steel
  • Other gauges and types of stainless steel available to meet the function and chemical resistant demands of highly specialized labs
  • Countertops have galvanized steel reinforcing hat channels
  • Sound deadening tape is factory-installed
  • Top support options include NSF-listed sprayed latex sound deadening and marine grade plywood backing with white laminate facing
  • Standard front edge Square or Box Marine, unless otherwise specified
  • Fabricated sink bowls available in most any size and depth with single or multiple compartments
  • Both L-shaped and U-shaped tops are available per your drawings. Corners are mitered and factory welded

Backsplash

  • Standard height of back and end splashes is 4 ½”, unless otherwise specified
  • Back and end splashes are manufactured per specification
  • Either a mechanical hairline seam or field welded joint available per your specifications. Maximum length without seam is 144”. Length is reduced by 5 ½” for each end splash that may be required. Complete field welding and finishing services are available at additional expense.
  • For backsplash mounted faucets, splash will need to be at least 2” deep for plumbing access, holes for deck mounted faucets are typically centered 1 ¼” from the edge of the sink bowl.
  • Standard packaging is wood reinforced cardboard and is included in the cost. Full crating available.

Properties.Name: Family Design
Properties.Value:
The Southwest Solutions Group casework line is designed to be highly flexible and adaptable with every Revit model built to reflect its real world counterpart. Once loaded, each model has a variety of parameters which allow you to easily manipulate and customize various aspects of the casework design without ever needing to load a type catalog ever again.

Such features include:

  • Quickly Manipulate Sizes
  • Toe Kick Options
  • Door Styles
  • Handle Types
  • Lock Options
  • Angled Top Options
  • Material Options

In addition, each model comes with a high level of information built in, including a worst-case budget price that dynamically updates as you manipulate the model within Revit. This allows the designer and client to quickly understand where the money is being spent.  Also, within each model type, there are links to more detailed information should you need it. Having this level of flexibility combined with a high level of information is truly what BIM is meant to be.

Properties.Name: Technical Data
Properties.Value:
Sustainability

  • Particleboard and MDF fabricated from recycled wood waste material
  • Cardboard packaging made from recycled materials
  • Unusable pallets are recycled
  • All aluminum scrap is recycled
  • All adhesives used are water-based
  • Products meet low VOC standards
  • Powder coat paint is used on all metal surfaces

Construction

  • Cabinets are constructed of ¾” thick industrial grade 40-50lb substrate, double-faced melamine
  • All exposed edges are covered with 2mm PVC edge banding
  • All panels are connected with hafele mini-fix cam hidden fastener system
  • All cabinets are rail mounted for ease of install
  • Work surfaces are constructed of 1 1/16” thick high-pressure laminate

Parameters.Name: SSG_Short Description
Parameters.Value: Stainless Steel Single Bowl Drop In Sink w/ Ledge

Parameters.Name: SSG_Long Description
Parameters.Value: The single bowl drop in sink with faucet ledge is made of 18 gauge type 304, 18-8, stainless steel. The family comes in several preset sizes to make finding the right sink easy. The family is faced based to make it easy to place sink into counters while automatically cutting out it's mounting hole.
